The paper discusses user interface design and prototyping for seniors, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also focuses on teaching seniors about software design, which could be categorized under computer science education (cs.ED). The study analyzes the learning process of older adults, which could be classified under graphics (cs.GR) and cybernetics (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper proposes guidelines for teaching abstract technology-related concepts, which could be categorized under social and information sciences (cs.SI).
